t = int(input())
for i in range(t):
    c = input()
    v = c.split(' ')
    x = int(v[0])
    y = int(v[1])
    k = int(v[2])
    if x % k == 0 and y % k == 0:
        print('YES')
    else:
        print('NO')

T = int(input())
for _ in range(T):
    (x, y, K) = map(int, input().split())
    print('YES') if abs(x) % K == 0 and abs(y) % K == 0 else print('NO')

t = int(input())
for _ in range(t):
    (x, y, k) = map(int, input().split())
    print('NO') if abs(x) % k != 0 or abs(y) % k != 0 else print('YES')
